            <h2>About Me</h2>
            <p>I am a passionate and innovative BFA Design & Technology student at Parsons School of Design. My work explores the intersection of fashion and technology, driving forward concepts that merge creativity with functionality. With a background in merchandising, branding, and creative direction, I specialize in UI/UX design, digital marketing, and trend forecasting.</p>
            <p>Throughout my journey, Iâ€™ve developed expertise in translating visionary concepts into impactful, tech-driven solutions. From my coursework at Parsons to professional experiences with renowned brands like Ralph Lauren and J.Crew, I have honed my ability to combine design with storytelling to create meaningful connections.</p>
            <p>When I'm not designing, you can find me exploring the latest tech innovations, diving into trend analysis, or imagining how technology can redefine our daily experiences. My ultimate goal is to contribute to projects that push the boundaries of fashion, technology, and human interaction.</p>
